title: UK overall inflation remains at 3.8% in August, but food price growth climbs for fifth month in a row - business live
summary: Food prices have surged at their fastest pace since January 2024, driven primarily by increases in vegetables, milk, cheese, and fish. The Bank of England is anticipated to maintain current interest rates during its upcoming meeting on Thursday. This inflation in food costs reflects ongoing economic pressures impacting consumers.

title: Israel says it has opened ‘temporary’ route for residents to flee Gaza City after launching ground offensive – Middle East crisis live
